      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/35a633/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2024-04-22T19:57:42.122Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Due to limited BT options I am trying to use the Bridge Sensor function on my Elite Suito smart trainer.</p>\n<p>Does TrainerDay support bridge sensors through a smart trainer? My intension is to get HR and Cadence data through the smart trainer to TrainerDay (on Android Phone) using 1  BT connection.</p>\n<p>More Context:<br>\nThis is what I am trying to accomplish for indoor training:</p>\n<p>Connect my smart trainer to the following sensors:<br>\nGarmin HR strap<br>\nGarmin Cadence Sensor</p>\n<p>Connect to Garmin 530 Computer:<br>\nGarmin HR strap<br>\nGarmin Cadence<br>\nElite Smart Trainer (Power only)</p>\n<p>Connected to TrainerDay for ERG mode (Android phone):<br>\nSmart Trainer (Bridging HR and Cadence to TrainerDay)</p>\n<p>No data transfer between Garmin computer and phone until activity is completed.</p>\n<p>Is this possible? Is there another solution?<br>\nThanks!</p>",
